UID:ajf7cj5q5hg353bkfc2hg7ql1k@google.com
CREATED:20170301T210832Z
DESCRIPTION:Regional Fair for students with disabilities - helping prepare 
 families for life beyond high school: job training\, continuing education\,
  living options and more. Contact Carol Huntley carol_huntley@roundrockisd.
 org or Candy Squilla candy_squilla@roundrockisd.org for more information. E
 n espanol\, contact Rosie Beattie at rosie_beatty@roundrockisd.org\n\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20170301T210832Z
LOCATION:Round Rock High School 100 Building\, 300 Lake Creek Drive\, Round
  Rock\, TX
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Destination...Life Regional Transition Fair
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20160227T150000Z
DTEND:20160227T193000Z
DTSTAMP:20260427T233835Z
UID:5660tcubf95335ed7sc7eapbks@google.com
CREATED:20160212T195009Z
DESCRIPTION:Round Rock ISD\, in conjunction with local school districts and
  organizations\, will host the “Destination...LIFE” Regional Transition Fai
 r Feb. 27 for students and families who receive special education services.
  \n\nRRISD has partnered with Austin ISD\, East Williamson County Co-op\, G
 eorgetown ISD\, Hutto ISD\, Manor ISD\, Lake Travis ISD\, Leander ISD and P
 flugerville ISD for the event\, which will be held from 9 a.m. to 1:30 p.m.
  in the Round Rock High School 100 building\, 300 Lake Creek Drive\, Round 
 Rock.  \n\nThe event will feature more than 75 booths for agencies and orga
 nizations that serve disabilities\, including Texas Department of Aging and
  Disability Services\, Texas Department of Assistive and Rehabilitative Ser
 vices\, Austin Community College\, Marbridge\, St. David’s Adaptive Driving
  Program and Texas Parent to Parent. Representatives from day activity cent
 ers and group homes will also be available. Since many services have long w
 aiting lists (some up to 15 years long)\, it is recommended that parents of
  students with disabilities of all ages attend and get the latest informati
 on on services.\n\nSpeaker sessions and panel discussions will be taking pl
 ace on topics of interest throughout the day\, including adult living optio
 ns\, Medicaid waiver programs\, guardianship options and other topics. This
  event is appropriate for parents and students receiving special education 
 of all ages\, from preschool through high school and 18 services. The event
  is free and all are welcome.
LAST-MODIFIED:20160212T195009Z
LOCATION:Round Rock High School 100 building\, 300 Lake Creek Drive\, Round
  Rock
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Regional Transition Fair
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
