DTSTAMP:20260427T233835Z
UID:j9il2m9q3a1mk37enqoabrjhts@google.com
CREATED:20150130T140442Z
DESCRIPTION:Round Rock ISD\, in conjunction with Austin ISD\, East Williams
 on County Co-op\, Georgetown ISD\, Hutto ISD\, Manor ISD\, Lago Vista ISD\,
  Lake Travis ISD\, Leander ISD and Pflugerville ISD will be presenting Dest
 ination...LIFE\, a Regional Transition Fair for students receiving special 
 education services and their families on Saturday\, March 7 from 9:00 a.m. 
 to 1:30 p.m.  This event will be held in Round Rock High School's Building 
 100 Commons Area.  This is the "old" entrance to Round Rock High School.\n\
 nDestination...LIFE will feature over 75 booths of agencies and organizatio
 ns serving students with disabilities\, including Texas Department of Aging
  and Disability Services\, Texas Department of Assistive and Rehabilitative
  Services\, ACC\, Easter Seals\, Goodwill\, Marbridge\, St. David's Adaptiv
 e Driving Program\, Texas Parent to Parent as well as representatives from 
 many day activity centers\, group homes and service providers.\n\nSpeaker s
 essions and panel discussions will be taking place during the day as well\,
  on topics of interest\, including Adult Living Options\, Medicaid Waiver P
 rograms\, Guardianship Options and others.\n\nThe event is free and all are
  welcome!
LAST-MODIFIED:20150130T140442Z
LOCATION:Round Rock High School\, 201 Deep Wood Drive\, Round Rock\, TX 786
 81\, United States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Destination...LIFE\, a Regional Transition Fair
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
