UID:1k928bcur1uiihhv4cv9nmc5k8@google.com
CREATED:20160401T135538Z
DESCRIPTION:The Empty Bowls model involves artists creating and donating ce
 ramic bowls\, then serving a meal at a community event. Guests choose a one
 -of-a-kind bowl to use and keep as a reminder of all the empty bowls in the
  world. In exchange for the meal and the bowl\, guests contribute a suggest
 ed minimum donation. 100% of proceeds are devoted to local hunger-fighting 
 organizations- in our case\, the Round Rock Area Serving Center.\n\nAll are
  invited to attend the Festival to choose from over 1000 handmade bowls\, s
 hare a simple meal of soup and bread\, enjoy local entertainment\, and make
  a donation to support the Round Rock Serving Center. \n\nFor more informat
 ion\, visit The Empty Bowl site.
LAST-MODIFIED:20160401T135538Z
LOCATION:Cedar Ridge High School\, 2801 Gattis School Rd\, Round Rock\, TX 
 78664\, United States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Round Rock Empty Bowls Festival
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
