BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20151111T000000Z
DTEND:20151111T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260427T233835Z
UID:vkttlrf01jjljqnk6t4grs6ohs@google.com
CREATED:20151110T163616Z
DESCRIPTION:Round Rock ISD parents are invited to a lecture on child and ad
 olescent mental health Nov. 10 at Round Rock High School.\n\nThe event will
  be held 6-7:30 p.m. in the Round Rock High School 700 building\, 300 North
  Lake Creek Drive\, Round Rock.\n\nThe lecture is presented by the Johns Ho
 pkins’ Adolescent Depression Awareness Program and the David Raymond Price 
 Foundation. Dr. Karen Swartz\, a mood disorders specialist from Johns Hopki
 ns\, will discuss mood and anxiety disorders in young people.\n\nTopics wil
 l include characteristics\, symptoms\, prevalence and treatment of bipolar 
 disorder\, depression and anxiety disorders. Time will be provided for ques
 tions and answers.\n\nPlease note that while all parents and adults are wel
 come\, the program is not appropriate for children or adolescents.\n\n\nhtt
 ps://roundrockisd.org/rrisd-hosts-adolescent-mental-health-lecture-for-pare
 nts/
LAST-MODIFIED:20151110T163619Z
LOCATION:Round Rock High School 700 building\, 300 North Lake Creek Drive\,
  Round Rock.
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:ADAP Lecture
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
