BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20141011T131500Z
DTEND:20141012T024500Z
DTSTAMP:20260427T233835Z
UID:p877vpci54i99f8gfm3q88c69g@google.com
CREATED:20141010T125942Z
DESCRIPTION:The Cedar Ridge High School band is hosting the Texas Marching 
 Classic\, the first of its kind in central Texas\, created to keep up with 
 the trends of the progressive high school marching band. The volunteer run 
 competition includes area high school bands competing during both prelimina
 ry and finals competitions. Top bands receive trophies and also compete for
  captions of Individual and Ensemble Music\, Individual and Ensemble Visual
 \, General Effect\, Percussion\, and Auxiliary. The event takes place at Ke
 lly Reeves Sports Complex. Gates open at  8:15 am with the first prelim per
 formance at 8:45 am until awards at 4:00 pm.  Finals begin at 6:40 pm – 10 
 pm.  Tickets for Prelims only: Students/Seniors $6\, Adults $10   Finals on
 ly: Students/Seniors $6\, Adults $10  or All Day Ticket: Students/Seniors $
 10\, Adults $15  \nCompeting bands registered for the 2014 competition incl
 ude high school bands from Austin\, Cedar Park\, Fredericksburg\, Georgetow
 n\, Sugar Land and other central Texas communities in addition to McNeil an
 d Westwood from RRISD.  Come out and enjoy watching the 22 plus bands of ap
 proximately 3700 high school students that will be performing throughout th
 e day.
LAST-MODIFIED:20141010T125942Z
LOCATION:Cedar Ridge High School\, 2801 Gattis School Rd\, Round Rock\, TX 
 78664\, United States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Cedar Ridge Hosts 3rd Annual Texas Marching Classic
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
