DESCRIPTION:Round Rock ISD’s Department of Gifted and Advanced Academic Ser
 vices will present its second Independent Study Project Showcase and Parent
  Seminar of the year Thursday\, January 30. The event is from 6 to 7:30 p.m
 . at Cedar Valley Middle School\, 8139 Racine Trail\, Austin. Student proje
 cts from Berkman\, Bluebonnet\, Brushy Creek\, Cactus Ranch\, Chandler Oaks
 \, Deep Wood\, England\, Fern Bluff\, Great Oaks\, Old Town and Sommer elem
 entary schools will be on display. At 6:45 p.m.\, Deborah Mersino will disc
 uss “Why Screen Time Isn’t Evil: How Advanced Learners Can Benefit from Tec
 hnology Literacy – What Parents Need to Know.”
LAST-MODIFIED:20140123T222441Z
LOCATION:Cedar Valley Middle School\, 8139 Racine Trail\, Austin\, TX\, Uni
 ted States
