DTEND:20160406T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260427T233835Z
UID:hvfe8c3l7a5ii5eg76s38ktc6o@google.com
CREATED:20160401T134108Z
DESCRIPTION:The Round Rock ISD Construction and Community Relations teams w
 ill be hosting a community meeting for the Brushy Creek and Avery Ranch com
 munities in regards to the construction of its 11th middle school.\n\nMiddl
 e School No. 11 will open in August 2017 on Pearson Ranch Road\, next to El
 sa England Elementary School. The school was a part of the $299 million bon
 d initiative approved in May 2014. \n\nThe community meeting will be held o
 n Tuesday\, April 5 at 7:00 p.m. at Brushy Creek MUD located at 16318 Great
  Oaks Drive\, Round Rock. The meeting will include a presentation on the co
 nstruction of the school and an opportunity for community members to ask qu
 estions. \n\nFor more information on Middle School No. 11 construction and 
 all bond projects\, please visit bond.roundrockisd.org.\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20160401T134108Z
LOCATION:Brushy Creek MUD\, 16318 Great Oaks Dr\, Round Rock\, TX 78681\, U
 nited States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Middle School No. 11 construction community meeting
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
