DESCRIPTION:<p dir="ltr"><b>Ten Things Not to Say to Your Gifted Child</b><
 /p><p dir="ltr">Words can be powerful motivators\, but they can also be pow
 erful discouragers\, especially for gifted students who may over-analyze ev
 ery word or suffer from imposter syndrome. Explore ten things that are comm
 only said by parents of gifted children\, the potential unintended conseque
 nces\, and what to say instead that conveys unconditional love\, establishe
 s a safe environment\, respects uniqueness\, and nurtures talent. This sess
 ion is based on a book of the same name by Nancy H. Heilbronner.</p><p dir=
 "ltr"><a href="https://meet.google.com/mhy-uozg-hfc?authuser=0&amp\;hs=122"
 >Join with Google Meet</a><br>meet.google.com/mhy-uozg-hfc</p><p dir="ltr">
 Join by phone<br>(US) +1 919-590-3435‬ PIN: ‪474 821 906‬#</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260402T193726Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Talented and Gifted Lunch and Learn 1
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
