UID:4cqthuudrolgqckc3085bgteac@google.com
CREATED:20130110T210057Z
DESCRIPTION:Round Rock ISD will host its fourth annual Music Faculty Recita
 l on Tuesday\, Jan. 22\, at 7 p.m. at the Round Rock ISD Performing Arts Ce
 nter located at 5800 McNeil Road in Austin. \n\nThe event is sponsored by t
 he Round Rock ISD student chapter of the Future Music Educators Association
 \, consisting of high school students who are interested in a career as mus
 ic educators. The RRISD Chapter of Texas Future Music Educators is comprise
 d of students from all five RRISD high schools. \n\nThe annual performance 
 is designed to provide an opportunity for students and the community to hea
 r our outstanding RRISD band\, choir\, and orchestra directors\, as well as
  elementary music teachers\, perform in public. The music will include solo
  performances as well as an eclectic variety of vocal and instrumental ense
 mbles. \n\n“This is a unique event\,” Round Rock ISD Fine Arts Director Jim
  Van Zandt said. “I’m not aware of any other school districts that actually
  produce faculty recitals.” \n\nAlthough the event is free to the public\, 
 donations will be accepted for a special fund that will help provide partia
 l scholarships for private music lessons for students that need financial a
 id.
LAST-MODIFIED:20230307T012116Z
LOCATION:Round Rock ISD Performing Arts Center 
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Music Faculty Recital
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
